Definition: with passionate fervor
Example: both those for and against are fervently convinced they speak for the great majority of the people; a fierily opinionated book
Synonyms: adj, all, passionate, fiery, fervently, fervent, fervidly, fervid, with, fervor, both, those, for, and, against, are, convinced, they, speak, the, great, majority, of, people, a, opinionated, book
Category: adv.all
